---
import Layout from '../../Base.astro';
import SimpleHero from '../../components/SimpleHero.astro';
import FeaturedArticles from '../../components/FeaturedArticles.astro';
import ServicesRelatedWork from '../../components/ServicesRelatedWork.astro';
import '../../styles/pages/_services-list.scss';
---

<Layout
  title="Audience Targeting | Florida Marketing Agency"
  description="Marketing gets expensive fast when you are talking to everyone. We identify the audiences most likely to care, convert, and justify the spend behind your campaigns."
>
  <SimpleHero
    tagline="Digital Marketing Services"
    title="Audience Targeting"
    description="Marketing gets expensive fast when you are talking to everyone. We identify the audiences most likely to care, convert, and justify the spend behind your campaigns."
    lottieFile="audience-targeting.json"
  />
  <div class="service-body">
    <div class="wrapper wrapper--narrow">
      <h2>Where teams get stuck</h2>
      <p>
        A lot of marketing underperforms because the audience is too broad. The message tries to reach everyone, the
        spend gets scattered, and the people seeing the campaign are not the people most likely to act.
      </p>
      <p>That makes every other decision harder, from creative direction to channel choice to budget allocation.</p>
      <h2>How we fix it</h2>
      <p>
        We look at the business, the offer, the existing data, and the behavior of the people you need to reach. From
        there we define clearer segments, identify what matters to each one, and shape targeting around real intent
        instead of guesses.
      </p>
      <h2>What moving forward looks like</h2>
      <p>If your team knows traffic is coming in but not the right traffic, we can audit your current audiences, tighten the targeting, and give each campaign a more defensible direction.</p>
      <p><a href="/contact/" class="button button--green">Clarify Your Audience</a></p>
    </div>
    <ServicesRelatedWork tag={77} />
  </div>
  <FeaturedArticles />
</Layout>
